    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Toxic substances used to eradicate fungi that damage crops or ornamental plants or endanger the health of animals or humans. Most fungicide is applied topically but systemic fungicides may be applied that are distributed throughout living tissues to eradicate or protect against disease. Fungicides may also be impregnated in textiles, paper, leather, or wood as well as painted on masonry and plaster.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047822/MFA Conservation and Art Material Encyclopedia Online: CAMEO (2005-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>用來滅除真菌的有毒物質，對農作物及觀賞植物有害，對於動物及人體也會造成傷害。大多數殺真菌劑為非系統性，只對有施放藥劑的部位產生作用，但系統性殺菌劑則可在活體組織內轉移以消滅或抵抗病菌。織品、紙張、皮革或木材上都可能含有殺真菌劑，甚至石材和塑膠上也可能塗有殺真菌劑。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
